<h1 class="main-title">
The Best Acne Treatment Approach Is Often Non-Prescription Acne Treatment Systems. Here’s Why… </h1>
<h2>We All Know The Basic Advice About Taking Care Of Acne</h2>
<ul>
<li>Scrub your face with soap</li>
<li>Don&#8217;t eat chocolate</li>
<li>Let the sun dry out your skin</li>
<li>Zap your zits with antibiotics</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The problem with this advice is that it&#8217;s wrong.</strong></p>
<figure id="attachment_4781" style="max-width: 766px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-full wp-image-4781" src="https://www.facingacne.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/38215087_ml.jpg" alt="" width="766" height="248" srcset="https://www.facingacne.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/38215087_ml.jpg 766w, https://www.facingacne.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/38215087_ml-300x97.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 766px) 100vw, 766px" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Most basic advice about acne is wrong!</figcaption></figure>
